From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: FMan policer profile install (productive, M3-3d)

Forward-port of the FMan PCD Policer (srTCM/trTCM three-colour-marker)
silicon programming path into the COMMON board patch stack (built-in for
default/vpp/ask via the FSL_FMAN_PCD config from patch 0092).  Re-anchors
the tested ask20 Policer-profile MURAM-encoding path (ask20 branch patches
0018 body-1 create/destroy + 0019 body-2 rate-encoder) onto the 0092 PCD
subsystem + 0097 KeyGen + 0098 CC + 0099 HM base, adapted to the dpaa1
flat-C policer API declared by board patch 0090a.  This is PR5 of the
dpaa1 PCD forward-port closing M3-3d.

What this adds
--------------
- fman_pcd_plcr.c (new, fsl_dpaa_fman.ko): the productive srTCM/trTCM
  profile installer.  Defines struct fman_pcd_plcr_profile + the 16-byte
  MURAM profile-record layout (RM 8.7.6 p.5: mode @0x0, CIR @0x4, CBS @0x8,
  EIR|EBS @0xc) and three static encoders: plcr_encode_rate() packs a
  bits/sec rate into the FMan exp<<29|mant<<13 field (scaled =
  ceil(bps*2^31/clk_hz), smallest exponent in [0..7] keeping the mantissa
  16-bit, saturating at exp=7/mant=0xffff on overflow, zero rate -> 0);
  plcr_encode_burst() quantises a byte burst to 256-byte units (round-up,
  saturate 0xffff); plcr_build_mode() assembles the PMR word (srTCM sets
  PIR_DISABLED, trTCM sets ALG_TRTCM, COLOR_AWARE honours frame colour).
  fman_pcd_plcr_install() encodes the rate/burst/mode BEFORE touching MURAM
  (CRITICAL: fman_get_clock_freq() returns u16 MHz so the body multiplies
  by 1_000_000 to get Hz — the ask20 PR14e-body-2 gotcha), allocates the
  16-byte record, writes it under a per-profile spinlock via four
  iowrite32be stores, and publishes the profile on pcd->plcr_profiles
  (replacing any existing (port, slot) — idempotent rebuild).
  fman_pcd_plcr_destroy() is idempotent: finds by (port, slot), zeroes the
  mode word to disarm metering, frees the MURAM, frees the handle.  The
  MURAM internals (fman_pcd_muram_alloc / fman_muram_offset_to_vbase, the
  latter NOT EXPORT_SYMBOL'd) stay inside this module — the 0097/0098/0099
  bridge idiom.

- include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h: publishes the neutral struct
  fman_pcd_plcr_hw_profile (host bps/bytes: trtcm, color_aware, cir_bps,
  cbs_bytes, pir_bps, pbs_bytes) + the two install/destroy prototypes.  The
  neutral struct lives in the public header so both fsl_dpa.ko (which owns
  the host-endian struct fman_policer_profile in dpaa_fman_caps.h) and
  fsl_dpaa_fman.ko can see it without a circular include.

- dpaa_fman_caps.c (fsl_dpa.ko): makes fman_policer_install() /
  fman_policer_destroy() productive.  install() gates on
  FMAN_CAP_POLICER_TRTCM (BIT2) BEFORE touching MURAM (spec sec 3.5),
  validates the inputs (cir_bps == 0 -> -EINVAL; a trTCM profile whose
  pir_bps < cir_bps -> -ERANGE), translates the host-endian struct
  fman_policer_profile into the neutral fman_pcd_plcr_hw_profile
  (dpaa_plcr_prof_to_hw(): mode TRTCM->trtcm, color AWARE->color_aware,
  rates/bursts verbatim), resolves the PCD via fman_get_pcd(fm), and
  delegates to fman_pcd_plcr_install().  destroy() gates on caps and
  delegates to the idempotent fman_pcd_plcr_destroy().

- Makefile: adds fman_pcd_plcr.o to the FSL_FMAN_PCD object list.

Rate/burst encoding note
------------------------
Rates are bits/sec and bursts are bytes at both the dpaa-side host ABI and
the neutral descriptor; the exp/mant rate-field quantisation and the
256-byte burst quantisation happen entirely in the fman-side encoder
(plcr_encode_rate / plcr_encode_burst), so the neutral struct carries plain
host values.  For srTCM the EIR rate half of the EIR|EBS word stays 0
(PIR_DISABLED is set in the mode word) and only the excess-burst (EBS)
mantissa is meaningful; for trTCM the EIR half carries the encoded peak
rate's high 16 bits.

Verified: native arm64 compile of drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/ and
.../dpaa/ with LOCALVERSION=-vyos is 0 warnings / 0 errors; fman_pcd_plcr.o,
dpaa_fman_caps.o and both built-in.a archives build clean; all four
EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL symbols (fman_pcd_plcr_install/destroy,
fman_policer_install/destroy) resolve.

Spec sec 5.6.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
index e366e85..3bb03bb 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
@@ -457,20 +457,89 @@ EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_hm_caps_supported);
  * install failure. Spec sec 5.6.
  * ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
 
+/*
+ * Translate the host-endian struct fman_policer_profile (private to
+ * fsl_dpa.ko) into the neutral struct fman_pcd_plcr_hw_profile the
+ * fman-side installer consumes.  The neutral fields carry HOST values
+ * (bits/sec, bytes); the fman-side encoder does the exp/mant rate-field
+ * and 256-byte burst quantisation.  mode TRTCM->trtcm, color AWARE->
+ * color_aware; rates/bursts copied verbatim.
+ */
+static void dpaa_plcr_prof_to_hw(const struct fman_policer_profile *prof,
+				 struct fman_pcd_plcr_hw_profile *hw)
+{
+memset(hw, 0, sizeof(*hw));
+hw->trtcm = (prof->mode == FMAN_POLICER_MODE_TRTCM);
+hw->color_aware = (prof->color_mode == FMAN_POLICER_COLOR_AWARE);
+hw->cir_bps = prof->cir_bps;
+hw->cbs_bytes = prof->cbs_bytes;
+hw->pir_bps = prof->pir_bps;
+hw->pbs_bytes = prof->pbs_bytes;
+}
+
+/*
+ * Productive policer install (spec sec 5.6).  Gates on
+ * FMAN_CAP_POLICER_TRTCM BEFORE touching MURAM per spec sec 3.5; on a
+ * board without it (mainline ucode 106) returns -ENOTSUPP so the flavor
+ * layer fails soft.  On the Mono Gateway DK the 210.10.1 QEF blob lights
+ * the policer up (caps = 0x17), so this path is live there.  Validates
+ * the rate/burst inputs (cir_bps == 0 -> -EINVAL; a trTCM profile whose
+ * pir_bps < cir_bps -> -ERANGE), translates the host-endian profile into
+ * the neutral descriptor, resolves the PCD via fman_get_pcd(fm), and
+ * delegates the silicon programming to fman_pcd_plcr_install() in
+ * fsl_dpaa_fman.ko (which owns the MURAM allocator + rate encoder).
+ */
 int fman_policer_install(struct fman *fm, u8 port_id, u8 profile_id,
  const struct fman_policer_profile *prof)
 {
-if (!prof)
+struct fman_pcd_plcr_hw_profile *hw;
+struct fman_pcd *pcd;
+int err;
+
+if (!fm || !prof)
 return -EINVAL;
+if (!fman_policer_caps_supported())
 return -ENOTSUPP;
+if (prof->cir_bps == 0)
+return -EINVAL;
+if (prof->mode == FMAN_POLICER_MODE_TRTCM &&
+    prof->pir_bps < prof->cir_bps)
+return -ERANGE;
+
+pcd = fman_get_pcd(fm);
+if (!pcd)
+return -ENXIO;
+
+hw = kzalloc(sizeof(*hw), GFP_KERNEL);
+if (!hw)
+return -ENOMEM;
+
+dpaa_plcr_prof_to_hw(prof, hw);
+
+err = fman_pcd_plcr_install(pcd, port_id, profile_id, hw);
+kfree(hw);
+return err;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_policer_install);
 
+/*
+ * Productive policer destroy (spec sec 5.6).  Gates on
+ * FMAN_CAP_POLICER_TRTCM, resolves the PCD and delegates to the
+ * idempotent fman_pcd_plcr_destroy() (a (port, slot) matching no live
+ * profile is a no-op).  No-op on a board without policer caps (nothing
+ * was ever installed).
+ */
 void fman_policer_destroy(struct fman *fm, u8 port_id, u8 profile_id)
 {
-/* idempotent no-op on stub; productive impl will validate slot and
- * detach the policer profile from any CC actions still referencing it.
- */
+struct fman_pcd *pcd;
+
+if (!fm)
+return;
+if (!fman_policer_caps_supported())
+return;
+pcd = fman_get_pcd(fm);
+if (pcd)
+fman_pcd_plcr_destroy(pcd, port_id, profile_id);
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_policer_destroy);
 
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/Makefile b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/Makefile
index 1428ed4..660fdef 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/Makefile
@@ -6,6 +6,6 @@ obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_FMAN) += fsl_dpaa_fman_port.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_FMAN) += fsl_dpaa_mac.o
 
 fsl_dpaa_fman-objs	:= fman_muram.o fman.o fman_sp.o fman_keygen.o
-fsl_dpaa_fman-$(CONFIG_FSL_FMAN_PCD) += fman_pcd.o fman_pcd_kg.o fman_pcd_cc.o fman_pcd_manip.o
+fsl_dpaa_fman-$(CONFIG_FSL_FMAN_PCD) += fman_pcd.o fman_pcd_kg.o fman_pcd_cc.o fman_pcd_manip.o fman_pcd_plcr.o
 fsl_dpaa_fman_port-objs := fman_port.o
 fsl_dpaa_mac-objs:= mac.o fman_dtsec.o fman_memac.o fman_tgec.o
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_plcr.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_plcr.c
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..c145af4
--- /dev/null
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_plcr.c
@@ -0,0 +1,399 @@
+// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0
+/*
+ * FMan PCD Policer (srTCM/trTCM) - three-colour-marker silicon programming.
+ *
+ * dpaa1 forward-port (PR5 of the PCD series closing M3-3d).  Re-anchors the
+ * tested ask20 Policer-profile MURAM-encoding path (ask20 branch patches
+ * 0018 body-1 create/destroy + 0019 body-2 rate-encoder) onto the 0092 PCD
+ * subsystem + 0097 KeyGen + 0098 CC + 0099 HM base, adapted to the dpaa1
+ * flat-C policer API declared by board patch 0090a:
+ *
+ *   enum fman_policer_mode { SRTCM, TRTCM }
+ *   struct fman_policer_profile { mode, color_mode, cir_bps, cbs_bytes,
+ *                                  pir_bps, pbs_bytes }
+ *
+ * The dpaa-side entry points (fman_policer_install / fman_policer_destroy in
+ * dpaa_fman_caps.c, fsl_dpa.ko) gate on FMAN_CAP_POLICER_TRTCM, translate
+ * their module-private host-endian struct fman_policer_profile into the
+ * neutral struct fman_pcd_plcr_hw_profile declared in
+ * <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>, and delegate to the two EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL entry
+ * points below (which live here in fsl_dpaa_fman.ko alongside the MURAM
+ * allocator, so the silicon internals never cross the module boundary -
+ * identical bridge idiom to fman_pcd_cc.c / fman_pcd_manip.c / fman_pcd_kg.c).
+ *
+ * Authoritative reference
+ * -----------------------
+ * - LS1046A Reference Manual sec 8.7.6   (Policer profile registers).
+ * - LS1046A Reference Manual sec 8.7.6 p.5 (16-byte trTCM profile record).
+ * - RFC 2697 (srTCM) / RFC 2698 (trTCM) marker semantics.
+ *
+ * Provenance
+ * ----------
+ * Mainline drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/ has zero policer code; the
+ * profile-record layout and the exp/mant rate-field encoding below are
+ * authored from the RM, cross-referenced against the legacy NXP SDK
+ * fm_plcr.{h,c} (read-only silicon-fact reference, no code copied).  The
+ * 16-byte profile record + PMR mode-word bits + rate exp<<29|mant<<13
+ * encoding mirror the validated ask20 fman_pcd_plcr.c PR14e bodies.
+ */
+
+#include <linux/err.h>
+#include <linux/errno.h>
+#include <linux/export.h>
+#include <linux/io.h>
+#include <linux/kernel.h>
+#include <linux/list.h>
+#include <linux/math64.h>
+#include <linux/module.h>
+#include <linux/mutex.h>
+#include <linux/slab.h>
+#include <linux/spinlock.h>
+#include <linux/types.h>
+
+#include <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>
+#include "fman.h"
+#include "fman_muram.h"
+#include "fman_pcd_internal.h"
+
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+/* Policer profile record layout - RM 8.7.6 p.5                        */
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+
+/*
+ * The policer profile is a 16-byte MURAM-resident record consumed by the
+ * FMan policer engine.  Word offsets within the record (all big-endian
+ * relative to the host):
+ *
+ *   0x0  u32 mode  - PMR (profile mode register) bits
+ *   0x4  u32 cir   - committed information rate field (exp<<29|mant<<13)
+ *   0x8  u32 cbs   - committed burst size field (256-byte units)
+ *   0xc  u32 eir_ebs - peak/excess rate (hi 16) | peak/excess burst (lo 16)
+ *
+ * Cross-ref SDK fm_plcr.h::t_FmPcdPlcrProfileRegs (16-byte packed struct).
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PROFILE_SIZE	16
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_OFF_MODE	0x0
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_OFF_CIR	0x4
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_OFF_CBS	0x8
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_OFF_EIR_EBS	0xc
+
+/*
+ * PMR (profile mode register) bits - RM 8.7.6 + cross-ref SDK fm_plcr.h
+ * FM_PCD_PLCR_PMR_*.  COLOR_AWARE honours the incoming frame colour;
+ * ALG_TRTCM selects the two-rate marker (clear = srTCM single-rate);
+ * PIR_DISABLED is set for srTCM so the engine ignores the EIR field.
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PMR_COLOR_AWARE	0x8000u
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PMR_ALG_TRTCM	0x2000u
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PMR_PACKET_MODE	0x1000u
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PMR_PIR_DISABLED	0x0040u
+
+/*
+ * Rate-field exp/mant encoding (RM 8.7.6 + cross-ref SDK fm_plcr.h).  The
+ * rate register packs a 3-bit exponent at bit 29 and a 16-bit mantissa at
+ * bit 13.  The encoded value approximates:
+ *
+ *   rate_field ~= (bps * 2^31 / fman_clk_hz)
+ *
+ * scaled into the smallest exponent in [0..7] that keeps the mantissa
+ * within 16 bits; on overflow the field saturates at exp=7, mant=0xffff
+ * (the silicon ceiling).
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_EXP_SHIFT	29
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_EXP_MAX	7
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_MANT_SHIFT	13
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_MANT_MAX	0xffffu
+
+/* Burst sizes are quantised to 256-byte units (RM 8.7.6). */
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_BURST_UNIT_BYTES	256u
+#define FMAN_PCD_PLCR_BURST_MANT_MAX	0xffffu
+
+/**
+ * struct fman_pcd_plcr_profile - one MURAM-resident policer profile.
+ * @node:        anchor on pcd->plcr_list (protected by pcd->lock)
+ * @pcd:         owning PCD subsystem; back-pointer for MURAM free
+ * @port_id:     the FMan port this profile was installed for (bookkeeping)
+ * @profile_id:  caller-chosen silicon slot id (0..255)
+ * @record_off:  MURAM byte offset of the 16-byte profile record (the value
+ *               a CC action's policer-pointer carries per spec sec 5.4)
+ * @record:      CPU-visible iomem pointer to the profile record
+ * @lock:        per-profile spinlock guarding the record writes
+ *
+ * Definition is private to this translation unit.
+ */
+struct fman_pcd_plcr_profile {
+	struct list_head	node;
+	struct fman_pcd	*pcd;
+	u8		port_id;
+	u8		profile_id;
+	unsigned long	record_off;
+	void __iomem	*record;
+	spinlock_t	lock;
+};
+
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+/* Rate / burst field encoders - RM 8.7.6                              */
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+
+/*
+ * Encode a bits-per-second rate into the FMan exp<<29|mant<<13 field.
+ *
+ * scaled = DIV_ROUND_UP(bps * 2^31, fman_clk_hz); then find the smallest
+ * exponent in [0..7] such that (scaled >> exp) fits in 16 bits.  Saturate
+ * at exp=7, mant=0xffff on overflow.  A zero rate encodes to 0x00000000.
+ *
+ * CRITICAL: fman_get_clock_freq() returns u16 MHz, NOT Hz - the caller
+ * multiplies by 1_000_000 before passing @clk_hz here (ask20 PR14e-body-2
+ * gotcha, 2026-05-14).
+ */
+static u32 plcr_encode_rate(u64 bps, u64 clk_hz)
+{
+	u64 scaled;
+	u32 exp;
+	u64 mant;
+
+	if (bps == 0 || clk_hz == 0)
+		return 0;
+
+	/* scaled = ceil(bps * 2^31 / clk_hz). */
+	scaled = div64_u64((bps << 31) + clk_hz - 1, clk_hz);
+
+	for (exp = 0; exp <= FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_EXP_MAX; exp++) {
+		mant = scaled >> exp;
+		if (mant <= FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_MANT_MAX)
+			return ((u32)exp << FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_EXP_SHIFT) |
+			       ((u32)mant << FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_MANT_SHIFT);
+	}
+
+	/* Overflow: saturate at the silicon ceiling. */
+	return ((u32)FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_EXP_MAX <<
+		FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_EXP_SHIFT) |
+	       ((u32)FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_MANT_MAX <<
+		FMAN_PCD_PLCR_RATE_MANT_SHIFT);
+}
+
+/*
+ * Encode a burst size (bytes) into a 16-bit mantissa of 256-byte units.
+ * Rounds up so a burst is never under-provisioned; saturates at 0xffff.
+ */
+static u16 plcr_encode_burst(u32 bytes)
+{
+	u32 units;
+
+	if (bytes == 0)
+		return 0;
+
+	units = DIV_ROUND_UP(bytes, FMAN_PCD_PLCR_BURST_UNIT_BYTES);
+	if (units > FMAN_PCD_PLCR_BURST_MANT_MAX)
+		units = FMAN_PCD_PLCR_BURST_MANT_MAX;
+	return (u16)units;
+}
+
+/*
+ * Assemble the PMR (profile mode register) word from the neutral profile.
+ * srTCM clears ALG_TRTCM and sets PIR_DISABLED; trTCM sets ALG_TRTCM.
+ * COLOR_AWARE is set when the caller requested colour-aware marking.
+ * Byte-mode metering is the default (PACKET_MODE clear).
+ */
+static u32 plcr_build_mode(const struct fman_pcd_plcr_hw_profile *hw)
+{
+	u32 pmr = 0;
+
+	if (hw->color_aware)
+		pmr |= FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PMR_COLOR_AWARE;
+
+	if (hw->trtcm)
+		pmr |= FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PMR_ALG_TRTCM;
+	else
+		pmr |= FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PMR_PIR_DISABLED;
+
+	return pmr;
+}
+
+/*
+ * Write the 16-byte profile record into MURAM (RM 8.7.6 p.5).  Four
+ * iowrite32be stores under the profile's spinlock.  The EIR/EBS word
+ * packs the peak/excess rate field in the high 16 bits and the
+ * peak/excess burst mantissa in the low 16 bits; for srTCM the rate
+ * half is zero (PIR_DISABLED is set in the mode word) and only the
+ * excess-burst (EBS) half is meaningful.
+ *
+ * NOTE: the four stores are not a single atomic transaction - a tearing
+ * window exists between them where the engine could observe a partial
+ * update.  This is acceptable because the profile is not armed until a
+ * CC action's policer-pointer references record_off (spec sec 5.4), which
+ * happens strictly after this writer returns.
+ */
+static void plcr_program_record(void __iomem *rec, u32 mode, u32 cir,
+				u32 cbs, u32 eir_ebs)
+{
+	iowrite32be(mode, rec + FMAN_PCD_PLCR_OFF_MODE);
+	iowrite32be(cir, rec + FMAN_PCD_PLCR_OFF_CIR);
+	iowrite32be(cbs, rec + FMAN_PCD_PLCR_OFF_CBS);
+	iowrite32be(eir_ebs, rec + FMAN_PCD_PLCR_OFF_EIR_EBS);
+}
+
+/* Find an installed profile for (@port_id, @profile_id).  Caller holds
+ * pcd->lock.
+ */
+static struct fman_pcd_plcr_profile *
+plcr_find_locked(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 port_id, u8 profile_id)
+{
+	struct list_head *head = fman_pcd_get_plcr_list(pcd);
+	struct fman_pcd_plcr_profile *p;
+
+	if (!head)
+		return NULL;
+	list_for_each_entry(p, head, node)
+		if (p->port_id == port_id && p->profile_id == profile_id)
+			return p;
+	return NULL;
+}
+
+/**
+ * fman_pcd_plcr_install() - program one srTCM/trTCM policer profile.
+ * @pcd:     the PCD subsystem (from fman_get_pcd())
+ * @port_id: the FMan port the profile is installed for
+ * @profile_id: caller-chosen silicon slot id (0..255)
+ * @hw:      neutral profile spec (host bps/bytes; this body encodes them)
+ *
+ * Allocates a 16-byte MURAM profile record, encodes the exp/mant rate
+ * fields + 256-byte burst mantissas + PMR mode word per RM 8.7.6, writes
+ * the record, and registers the profile on pcd->plcr_list so
+ * fman_pcd_release() reaps it on unbind.  Re-installing on a slot that is
+ * already populated for this port first tears the old profile down
+ * (idempotent rebuild).
+ *
+ * Return: 0 on success; negative errno on failure.
+ *
+ * RM 8.7.6 + cross-ref SDK fm_plcr.c FmPcdPlcrProfileSet().
+ */
+int fman_pcd_plcr_install(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 port_id, u8 profile_id,
+			  const struct fman_pcd_plcr_hw_profile *hw)
+{
+	struct fman_pcd_plcr_profile *p, *old;
+	struct muram_info *muram;
+	struct mutex *pcd_lock;
+	unsigned long flags;
+	unsigned long off;
+	void __iomem *vb;
+	u32 mode, cir, cbs, eir_ebs;
+	u32 eir_field;
+	u16 ebs_mant;
+	u64 clk_hz;
+	long err;
+
+	if (!pcd || !hw)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	muram = fman_get_muram(fman_pcd_get_fman(pcd));
+	if (!muram)
+		return -ENXIO;
+
+	/* fman_get_clock_freq() returns u16 MHz; scale to Hz. */
+	clk_hz = (u64)fman_get_clock_freq(fman_pcd_get_fman(pcd)) * 1000000ULL;
+
+	/* Encode the rate / burst / mode fields before touching MURAM. */
+	mode = plcr_build_mode(hw);
+	cir = plcr_encode_rate(hw->cir_bps, clk_hz);
+	cbs = (u32)plcr_encode_burst(hw->cbs_bytes);
+
+	/* trTCM: EIR rate (hi 16) | PBS burst mantissa (lo 16).
+	 * srTCM: EIR rate field stays 0 (PIR_DISABLED set); only the EBS
+	 * burst mantissa half is meaningful.
+	 */
+	if (hw->trtcm)
+		eir_field = plcr_encode_rate(hw->pir_bps, clk_hz) >> 16;
+	else
+		eir_field = 0;
+	ebs_mant = plcr_encode_burst(hw->pbs_bytes);
+	eir_ebs = (eir_field << 16) | (u32)ebs_mant;
+
+	p = kzalloc(sizeof(*p), GFP_KERNEL);
+	if (!p)
+		return -ENOMEM;
+	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&p->node);
+	spin_lock_init(&p->lock);
+	p->pcd = pcd;
+	p->port_id = port_id;
+	p->profile_id = profile_id;
+
+	off = fman_pcd_muram_alloc(pcd, FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PROFILE_SIZE);
+	if (IS_ERR_VALUE(off)) {
+		err = (long)off;
+		kfree(p);
+		return (int)err;
+	}
+	vb = (void __iomem *)fman_muram_offset_to_vbase(muram, off);
+	if (!vb) {
+		fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, off, FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PROFILE_SIZE);
+		kfree(p);
+		return -ENXIO;
+	}
+	p->record_off = off;
+	p->record = vb;
+
+	/* Zero then program the record under the profile spinlock. */
+	spin_lock_irqsave(&p->lock, flags);
+	memset_io(vb, 0, FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PROFILE_SIZE);
+	plcr_program_record(vb, mode, cir, cbs, eir_ebs);
+	spin_unlock_irqrestore(&p->lock, flags);
+
+	/* Publish: replace any existing profile for this (port, slot). */
+	pcd_lock = fman_pcd_get_lock(pcd);
+	mutex_lock(pcd_lock);
+	old = plcr_find_locked(pcd, port_id, profile_id);
+	if (old) {
+		list_del(&old->node);
+		fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, old->record_off,
+				    FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PROFILE_SIZE);
+		kfree(old);
+	}
+	list_add_tail(&p->node, fman_pcd_get_plcr_list(pcd));
+	mutex_unlock(pcd_lock);
+
+	return 0;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_plcr_install);
+
+/**
+ * fman_pcd_plcr_destroy() - tear down one policer profile by slot.
+ * @pcd:     the PCD subsystem
+ * @port_id: the FMan port (matched against the profile for safety)
+ * @profile_id: the silicon slot id to release
+ *
+ * Idempotent: a (port, slot) matching no live profile is a no-op.  Zeroes
+ * the profile record's mode word first so the engine stops metering
+ * before the MURAM is freed (defensive; the CC action that pointed here
+ * must already have been rewritten by the caller).
+ *
+ * RM 8.7.6 + cross-ref SDK fm_plcr.c FmPcdPlcrProfileDelete.
+ */
+void fman_pcd_plcr_destroy(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 port_id, u8 profile_id)
+{
+	struct fman_pcd_plcr_profile *p;
+	struct mutex *pcd_lock;
+	unsigned long flags;
+
+	if (!pcd)
+		return;
+
+	pcd_lock = fman_pcd_get_lock(pcd);
+	mutex_lock(pcd_lock);
+	p = plcr_find_locked(pcd, port_id, profile_id);
+	if (p)
+		list_del(&p->node);
+	mutex_unlock(pcd_lock);
+
+	if (!p)
+		return;
+
+	/* Disarm: zero the mode word so the engine stops metering. */
+	spin_lock_irqsave(&p->lock, flags);
+	iowrite32be(0, p->record + FMAN_PCD_PLCR_OFF_MODE);
+	spin_unlock_irqrestore(&p->lock, flags);
+
+	fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, p->record_off, FMAN_PCD_PLCR_PROFILE_SIZE);
+	kfree(p);
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_plcr_destroy);
